# The letter {{term|sc=Cyrl|твёрдый знак|tr=tvjórdyj znak||hard sign|lang=ru}}, the twenty-eighth letter of the [[Russian]] alphabet

====Usage notes====
In Russian, this letter has no sound of its own, but modifies that of the preceding consonant, causing it to be pronounced hard (i.e., unpalatalized). Some writers use <big>'</big> (apostrophe) instead of ъ, e.g. [[съезд]] — с'езд, which is considered non-standard. After the 1918 spelling reform when the usage of "ъ" was heavily reduced, some typewriters did not have the letter at all, forcing people to use <big>'</big> (apostrophe).

